l = [34, 23, 45, 56, 67, 78, 89] # This line creates a list 'l' with the values 34, 23, 45, 56, 67, 78, and 89. Lists are ordered collections of items that are mutable (can be changed after creation).
print(l) # This line prints the list 'l', which will output [34, 23, 45, 56, 67, 78, 89].

print(sum(l)) # This line calculates the sum of all the elements in the list 'l' using the built-in sum() function. The output will be 392, as it adds up all the numbers in the list.